casebody.data:
People v. Samuels. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

May 12, 1892.)

Argued before Bookstaver and Bischoff, JJ.

De Lancy Nieoll, for the People. Wm. J. Bayham, for defendant.

No opinion. Motion to vacate judgment entered on a forfeited recognizance granted. See 7 N. Y. Supp. 659; 18 N. Y. Supp. 951.
